title: Validate Discord ingress and derive canonical user identity
updated_at: "2026-07-13T02:07:35Z"
---
Acceptance: Treat a successfully authenticated Discord Gateway WSS session established with the configured bot token, Identify/Ready application identity, intents, session ID, and monotonic dispatch sequence as the production trust boundary. Derive the canonical actor from bot/application namespace plus immutable Discord user ID and guild scope where policy requires it; reject pre-Ready, wrong-application, bot/webhook, replayed or regressed sequence, invalid resume/session, malformed, DM-ambiguous, or display-only evidence. HTTP interaction signature verification remains a separate adapter if that ingress is enabled. Canonical contract: docs/plans/2026-07-13-github-user-attribution-and-feature-discovery.md.